	doi = {10.4018/979-8-3693-9420-5.ch010},
	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105011886240?origin=resultslist},
	abstract = {The use of machine learning algorithms to develop disease detection in the medical area is becoming increasingly popular due to its reliability and efficacy. The thyroid is an endocrine gland that generates hormones that aid in the body's metabolism management. Computer diagnosis plays a critical role in thyroid condition prediction, and this research examines the classification models utilized in thyroid disease. Classifying thyroid-related illnesses entails dividing them into groups according to their clinical manifestation, hormone levels, and underlying pathology. The timely identification and precise categorization of thyroid problems are crucial for efficient handling and therapy, given their substantial influence on an individual's standard of living. Comprehending the fundamental reasons, indications, and suitable diagnostic methods is essential for accurate categorization and the ensuing treatment measures. © 2025 by IGI Global Scientific Publishing. All rights reserved.},
